reviews.text: Such a moving and solemn atmosphere. I'm your visiting Amsterdam mainly for the nightlife and party scene, but a visit to the Anne Frank house in the daytime is well worth it. The museum was very informative and really helped to put the war and life of the people of this time into perspective. Reserve your tickets around 2 months in advance if your visiting. Better safe than sorry.

I was quite happy to get the ticket, even though I did not buy it in advance, but it is not easy, buy it in advance of two months, which is when 80% is made available. The other 20% are only available on the day from 9am on the site and it is always crowded! I got in at 9am on the site and in a matter of minutes the tickets are over. And the fact is: if you go to Amsterdam you can not miss the opportunity to visit this incredible memorial, a place of emotion, where the story is personified, being frighteningly close to our senses. The visit has schedule followed to scratch and is not allowed to take pictures of the Annex.

A very important history lesson which is even more disturbing when you visit the place. There are many contemporary testimonies which shut the mouth of each holocaust denier. After visiting the place it is now understandable why the tickets are only sold online. The demand is very high and they did a very good job to handle so many visitors. Keep up this important work!

Great experience walking through the house where this very inspirational girl lived while she and her family and two other families hid from the Nazis. Harrowing. But just reminded of the strength and awareness and hope during such a difficult time. Highly recommended during any visit to Amsterdam.

I've been here a couple of times and both times it was a sobering, but fantastic educational experience. 

It's theme and very serious setting aside, just the layout of the museum itself is superbly done - the audio tour guides you around the house step by step, explaining everything about the building, the events that happened there and the events that were occurring outside at the time. It doesn't let you get bored as you walk around and even my girlfriend, who hates museums of all sorts, absolutely loved coming to this place and it filled a very important gap in her knowledge of history.

I recommend this 10000% to anyone who visits Amsterdam. It is absolutely a must-see attraction.

This is a small museum that will make you very happy if you like cats. There are posters, statues, paintings etc. of and with cats and there are also three (?) real cats roaming around. The back yard is really beautiful and quiet! A lovely place to visit.

Pretty interesting building with nice interiors.
We have visited to see the back garden and inside of the house. But the cat collection was interesting too (and the real kitty as well!)

Seems like the place is trying to raise money for itself. Worth seeing. For art, interiors and the garden

Very little but nice museum with lots of pictures portraying cats. There are even a few pictures done by famous artists.
On the ground floor there is a shop with nice posters.

Must go place for every cat lover in the universe. It is really fascinating how many things were made with cat motifs. It is a relatively small museum with a great collection of cat items. Even my gf, a dog lover, agreed it was awesome and since then became a hidden convert.
Wonderful collection. Best museum for cat lovers. And if you're lucky you might see one of the resident cats 😸

Such a wonderful little museum with pipes from all over the world from different periods of time. A volunteer (forgot his name) guided us through the museum and we were very impressed by the width and depth of his knowledge. I highly recommend this place, for smokers and non-smokers alike.

It is a must!
Even if you do not smoke.

The museum is interesting,
they hold a huge collection of pipes from all around the world.

One member of the personal that works there is super nice,
he explains to you everything related to the pipes and their background.
Any question you have, he answers.
You learn a lot of different topics,
a history lesson in many aspects.

What a wonderful place to visit. I learned a lot. You are guided through this small museum with interesting stories and information. Well worth the visit. It is truly amazing to see the art on and of pipes.

A truly wonderous place to visit; the care, the attention and faithful preservation of the history of pipes is communicated with passion, intellect and insight. Questions are welcomed and given due attention and consideration.  A must to visit.

A very interesting museum showcasing the history of pipes over the centuries. A vast collection, very nicely displayed, and admission included a guided visit with a very knowledgeable guide. Museumkaart is accepted here and fully covers admission. A worthwhile visit.
Love the dancing buildings. And one is for sale! Only 1 950000.00 euros! A bargain to own a piece of a museum
Amazing centuries old church where Rembrandt was buried. The outside is beautiful  and the architecture is stunning. Loved my visit.
Beautiful landmark. Anne Frank house near by. Worth a visit.

A church that looks at society and is fully integrated with the environment and the present. It may seem like a little thing, but a church stretching high in your tower the gay pride flag is something!
The clock tower is a very nice aesthetic addition to the surrounding timely buildings and Westerkerk itself is a building of amazing design and history.

Walked by and on a whim went inside. I was warmly greeted and seated quickly. I enjoyed sitting at the window/bar seats to keep watching all the activities outside. The food was fantastic!! Very flavorful and quality ingredients. Reasonable price and food arrived quickly.

This place was downright delicious. A very nice location it a nice little store. You definitely might have to wait but that's due to its popularity. Very friendly and welcoming staff. Very great portion sizes and super delicious quality for good prices. Most definitely recommend!

There is a reason why this place is busy. Food and service are great. Order Banana almond chocolate sauce pancake as well as apple crumble ice cream pancake. The best sweet pancakes on the menu. Would recommend to anyone visiting Amsterdam. Bring your credit card, they don't take cash.

Had the Dutch pancakes with Bacon and Apples (#3)--very unique... Just don't expect to be served any Mrs. Butterworths!  Sat at one of the only two outdoor tables (they totally jammed us in behind some fat American girl that looked just like Hurley from "Lost") and had to put up with all the people waiting to be seated just staring at us while we ate.

The food 
American pancakes with bacon, a fried egg and maple syrup tasted good. The combination of savory and sweet was excellent. These pancakes were quite filling too. I asked them to serve the maple syrup separately to prevent the pancakes from getting soggy. 

My friends ordered the Dutch pancakes with bacon and cheese which they really liked too. 

The service and atmosphere 
The waiter was very friendly and nice. The restaurant was quite small, but very cozy. 

Price and rating 
American pancakes with bacon, fried egg and maple syrup €11,50 - 8/10
Dutch Pancakes with bacon and cheese €9,80 - 8/10

The food was extremely tasty and was an excellent way for my friend and I to further experience Dutch culture. The owner and our waitress were very welcoming and friendly - we ended up speaking with them for a while over our lunch. Awesome atmosphere, awesome food! Highly recommended!
Excellent service! I was profoundly shocked by the outstanding quality/price rate. Great place to eat in the perfect location.

My wife and I wandered into this restaurant our first day in Amsterdam . In case it wasn't obvious, were Americans and struggle with other languages (thanks public school) . The waiter came out just to greet us. He was incredibly friendly so we stopped for a meal, and man are we glad we did. Hot bread with homemade butter, a mashed potato pie with meatballs or goat cheese croquettes . It was a cold and rainy day and this meal was just the thing to shake off the cold. I don't think I can suggest this place any more. And the waiter named Kevin is a gem, friendly and helpful. 5 well deserved stars .

It’s really hard to find a local restaurant in the city. There’s not much restaurants of that kind, but De Blauwe is the one! Menus are cheap, food is great and you won’t be hungry at the end of the meal. The staff is welcoming. A lovely discovery!

We had lunch in this restaurant yesterday !! Two of my friends, my boyfriend and I ... Everything was going well: nice atmosphere, good food... Until the end of the meal, when our server made quite unpleasant questions and comments discriminative to gay people  when he found out my boyfriend and I were a couple and that totally ruined it for all of us!!

Take it!!! 🛶
The small, open and quiet sloops, really allow you to enjoy Amsterdam from the water. The skipper will be your guide and tells you amazing stories about Amsterdam 🇳🇱💦⛵️ .
Arguably the best way to experience Amsterdam. Cruising in the night makes you realize how big and inspirational the city is.

Like always know the canals of Amsterdam are a few of the main attractions, those are really beautiful, you can take a bout and spend a few hours taking thousand of amazing pictures or you can just walk through them.
Beautiful city. Beautiful weather. Pleasant.
One of its kind. Lovely and stunning
Tasty food and not spicy. If you want them spicy, you tell the waiter. Staff is very friendly and sincere. Lamb, vegetables and rice was fine. We paid 60 euros at dinner for 2 people.

Loved it here. Its a bit tucked away from the main Street and probably wouldn't have found it myself if it wasn't for a recommendation, but I'm really happy that we did find it. We went in for a quick bite but I would be very happy to spend the evening here nibbling on different courses. The owner is very proud and the food really good.  Nicely spiced and the sides are fresh. Definitely visit.
Great food! Friendly guy running the place, with everything looking tidy and having a proper Indian atmosphere. It feels warm and welcome.
Really great place to eat! Very friendly staff/owner, food is delicious. Be carefully with hot or very hot, the hot was already really hot for me 😅.
The best Indian food after long time in europe. Try the Butter Chicken and lamb shahi korma with peswaria naan amazing tasty.

Good food.  Nice ambience.  But watch the bill and the change made - they tried to rip us off 2x - once on the bill, charging us for things we never had, and once when they made change from my payment.  Be careful!
Good food. Original take on traditional Dutch food. Friendly, attentive service. Great location

Unfortunately the quality of the food was well below the level that would suit a restaurant with these prices. The meat was tough, vegetables and pumpkin overcooked and lacking taste, and the pâté had a not-so-fresh smell and taste to it. On the way to the bathroom, a look in the kitchen downstairs confirmed my expectations that had been created by the food quality. Although the wines were good they were also quite pricey. Service was friendly and attentive though. All in all: not recommended, just because of the bad food and uncorrespondingly high prices.
Erg duur voor wat je krijgt. De bediening vond ik hautin, personeel heeft een arrogante houding.
Sconsigliato, personalmente cucina dai sapori improponibili e prezzi elevati

Extremely poor. Very dated and tired restaurant. Bread came out and was stale.. hard as a rock. Food was greasy and just overall not appealing. Service was equally poor.. had to ask five people for the check, had multiple people ask for our order.. the restaurant wasn’t busy and somehow they managed to make things extremely complicated. Very very disappointed with the horrible food and poor service. Won’t be back

Paradiso is our family's go to place. We like their Sunday brunch and we have enjoyed their musical acts over many years. Their pizza is wood fired and delicious. Good consistent service and the food quality is very good.
The staff was considerate. Wide choice of menu items. Food was so fresh and came out fast! Full of flavor.
Had our school's annual staff appreciation dinner here. Great food and great service! Will return...
Nice place. Kid friendly space with the adjoining adult room. Good reliable place for Italian comfort food.

Really like this museum. The building itself is magnificent, outside and outside. The exhibitions are renewed often and always super interesting. Cool Japan, Mecca, Dutch colons were showed last time I went. There's a lot (too much) to see in one time. Despite that it never feels crowded because of how big the place is. They also have lockers which is very convenient.

Really interesting stop once you have seen the city center. Very family friendly, good for all ages. Probably the best museum in the city for science, culture, history, and art other than the gems in the city center! Not touristy

That was a very pleasant visit. The museum has a few very interesting expositions that discuss current controversial topics in the world. The price was reasonable and the facility is very well designed. Totally recommend.

A very vast collection of art from the colonial times up to modern times.
I personally really loved the exhibition about Japanese culture.
The museum is easy to navigate through, you won't get lost like in other museums, there are elevators if needed. Take your time and enjoy.

There are lockers for your stuff so you don't need to carry it.

Very good museum. They put lots thoughts and effort for each exhibit. Like it or not... I still appreciate all the efforts been put in. The museum building itself is a great space, it serve not only a place for display artifact but can be use for community and wide range of activities. I can be a dream house for arts and Cultural activities that really serve it's local community members.
It has some relief! It's not totally flat! That was amazing. I climbed up two meters, and it felt great. Lots of rabbits, very cute.
Nice views and a nice ride from town to city
Love these hills. Love the beach. Couldn’t be better given the proximity to Amsterdam. And it has a beach!
It is a true meaning to relax❤
Perfect!!!!

Beautiful location for a special event or for just sitting at the terrace. Service, and food are first-rate. Beautiful park surroundings. A quiet spot in Amsterdam, a bit out of the way but worth a visit
Lovely quiet spot for a coffee or lunch. Very helpful and friendly staff. Food and drinks were very good. Thanks for keeping my pencil case for me!

The entire estate is quite lovely considering it's a bastion of peace ans quiet so close to the centre of Amsterdam. However, the gardens are a but plain and the villa is in rather bad state on the inside. Sure they modernized it and have it serve the purpose of a venue for companies and private parties etc., But one would expect a bit more flair from such an historic estate, especially considering the many canal-houses that are so beautiful.

A lovely experience every time! The staff working in this building recognise the uniqueness and impact of the surroundings; their attention and friendliness seem like a beautiful framing to a work of art. And then there is the food; whether you're visiting for a coffee, a full meal, or an event, everything is delicious. The concept 'slow food' provides you an opportunity to take in your surroundings, have a deeper conversation and basically exhale. So take a little time and visit.

Good ingredients, well cooked, competent staff.
Obviously expensive, with reasons.

Ijburg it's a new town about 15 minutes from Amsterdam Central station via tram. It's an interesting architectural project and a calm place to have a break or small holiday with marina, beaches and sands.
love the transportation..so easy to travel into the city
Nice location close to Amsterdam
Pleasure island for living and raise children
New architecture, what can I say?
Busy but tasty and good selection, unless you are veggie... Quick service and nice staff. Sadly food was a little cold when it got to our table but still very nice

Awesome place with a huge variety of biers. It's a local place, which is a bit outside of the centre and far from the tourist crowd. Burgers are okay, but it is better not to try the chicken burger. Prices are OK, totally normal in Amsterdam.
Very nice place. Especially in sunny days the terrace is nice (and busy). Nice choice of beers on tap and bottle and burgers are also very decent.

Quite a solid selection of beer. Had the Mexican inspired burger which was pretty good, though slightly under seasoned. Large outdoor patio nice for a night out with friends. Very nice staff, great service.
Wow I love this place. Excellent service and YUMMY snacks!  Beer selection is 👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼

Very good service and polite stuff! An amazing spot to catch some sun on the terrace which is very cozy and well located!
Inside the bar, huge green plans and nice furniture turn the space into a relaxing and refreshing environment.
When it comes to the menu, we got the hamburger which was very tasty and well made. Stronly recommended!

Bar Botanique is located in East Amsterdam. With its open-air Dapper Market, Middle Eastern grocery stores and eateries, and hipster cafes, this neighborhood is great to explore. I stumbled upon Bar Botanique while strolling around and it’s a really cool place with a great selection of drinks and snacks/food. I especially love the greenery, tropical shirts worn by the staff and the vintage furniture! And service is quick and friendly.
Really nice soroundings and great service. Cocktails were so-and-so, but good and okay priced. Didn't try any food, but the dishes I saw looked great.

The food was a dissapointment. The pizza was average, i didn't really like the dough. More cheese and more toppings would make a huge difference. We also had the beetroot salad, which was tasty but too sour. However, it's a really nice place with good service.

This bar is one of the nicest in the eastern part of Amsterdam. Great decoration, good food (which isn’t overly expensive), fine wines and tasty cocktails. I would definitely recommend going there and to try the GT orange cinnamon.
İ was staying in their executive room but they told me its fully reserved. Such a stupid dutch situation
I ordered  a Medium steak and it was unfortunately almost well done. The steak was to dry. Location is great. The California Salad (starter) was nothing special.
Part of Mövenpick Amsterdam Hotel... Restaurant with good 4/6 star quality menu...
Just visited the bar,  which was on the verge of closing as I entered,  but was helped courteously and speedy.
Very friendly waiters good food

You'll fall in love with the place by the time you reach the ticket office, with its faithfully recreated 1900 decor. The museum would be worth a visit even without the pianolas, which are fascinating. Look out for pianola coffee concerts where you can listen to various rolls in an intimate atmosphere.

Fascinating collection of player pianos, honestly the best thing we did the whole week we were in Amsterdam - if you're into machines, music production, early 20th century music or, hell, even cowboy movies, you absolutely have to check this place out.

Apparently this collection is just the tip of the iceberg, too, they have thousands of piano rolls and hundreds of pianolas in storage and the very knowledgeable lady who talked us through the collection with great enthusiasm said they also do regular recitals and coffee morning concerts.
Amazing small and complete museum, where they know everything about pianola's. A must see if you like piano music

A treasure trove of cool stuff, this museum contains a handful of pianolas, hundreds of rolls, and an enthusiastic staff who will demonstrate it all to you. I was told they even have another hundred pianolas and thousands more manuscripts in storage!
The collection also included gramophones, and organ, and pianofortés.
Well worth the time to visit this unique and fascinating museum!
A little gem hidden away in de Jordaan district. Well worth a visit, pure nostalgia.
Only giving 2 stars because their bread is so good. Everything else leaves much to be desired. I've been here a few times and always below average service and food.
I was for few days in this location and the waitress was friendly and also the other things makes me happy :-). On my next Trip to Amsterdam i visit this location definitly again.
Food was amazing. Portions big. Friendly staff and decent prices. Not a lot to choose from when it comes to food though

The beautiful decor and feel of the place is soothing. You can enjoy good food that is pricey but fits the location and comfort as your sitting in comfortable sofas. Why three stars then? The answer as so often in this beautiful city is the same, the service or lack thereof. Inattentive you can watch the waiters chat with each other at the bar while your trying to catch their attention.

Three stars for decoration and 0 for food quality and service. It's worth having a drink here as it's a nice environment but don't be fooled the staff will forget about you and your orders and the food takes ages. Meatballs were cold

Really nice place to eat a good burger in peace. Not a lot of sitting place, but it wasn't crammed. The burgers are good and the ingredients freshly delivered every day. Special mention to the brownie, that really deserves more credit and attention.

Decided to stop by this place when we were passing by and looking for some lunch. The burgers were pretty good but the buns ruined the experience for me. The bread was kind of hard and didn’t go too well with the meat. The meat itself was great but I’d rethink the type of bread that is being used.
Neat and cozy place with very good service. Staff are friendly and speak English. I advise you try the truffle burger. I don't like truffles, but i loved the taste of that sandwich!

We were just wandering around, getting hungry and this sweet little shop came up to us. I must say one of the best burgers I ate till today, they have great recipes and do something to the onions what taste like an angels kiss. Full 5 stars from me and my gf. I recommend it to you

We were super hungry after walking around Amsterdam all day and we stumbled upon this place. I had a lamb burger, which was very good, and the fries were nice and crispy. And a good local beer as well. Oh, and they had a restroom which was nice. Because I didn't notice a lot of public restrooms around and I really had to pee!

Amazing burgers, cooked to perfection.  Their Green Flash IPA on tap us my go to beer.  Their fries are amazing and one of the few places that offer steak cut fries (and get that fresh garlic on it).  Anytime I'm on Solano and need a good burger, i look no further.  Always friendly staff and even when its busy, you get your food in a timely manner.  Love this place!

An excellent showing by a community based restaurant.  We shall start with the service.  It was good... bordering on excellent.  Ambiance was nice.  Food was excellent and plentiful. The voodoo sauce mixed with blue cheese added depth and fantastic sneak up on you heat. The large fry fed 3 people with left overs. All in all a solid good meal.  I will return.

Received attentive, if not nervous like, service and serving classically good Barney's Burgers  food. 
Perhaps it was the layout, the old athmosphere, the overly strong clinging perfume smell or the sticky feeling on the table but I cannot see myself returning to this particular Barney's on Solano.
So very good.  Best burger joint in the bay area

Barney's makes some of the best burgers I've had. Consistently. It's hard to describe exactly what they do so right, except that they capture the essence of an American burger. The classic Barney's Burger is big, juicy, slightly blackened, with fresh lettuce, tomato, and onion, on a perfect sesame bun. It's not edgy and over the top like a $25 artisanal gastropub burger. It's just damned good, and I keep coming back.

Delicious food and friendly staff. Service was very fast and meals had a good portion. Hip atmosphere and well mixed drinks. Veggie options are included and the meal started with an Appetizer on the house. Highly recommendable!
We had the BBQ rib of beef medium rare and the meat was delicious.
Well cooked steak, juicy and delicious. Desert was very good too with strong flavors that paired well.
Food is very geared towards the fashionable and healthy.
Love this place. Very good coffee nicely treated food

Its a very good rail station. In this station all transport you get like City Metro, Tram also long distance trail. In this station there have first class passenger waiting rood. Its enjoyable place. Thanks.

Amsterdam Centraal is the main station of Amsterdam. The famous places are nearby Amsterdam centraal.You can go by walk. Amsterdam Centraal is very well managed and you can get train for most of European cities. Information center is helpful. Tram station and bus station is also near by. You need ticket to get in and get out as there are automatic gate.

Clearly organized station. Connections between airport run all day long, 15 mins one way. If you arrive internationally, would suggestion you to take train to downtown then switch to Metro/Tram/Bus just outside of the station. Tickets machines is easy to find. Signs are straight forward and sufficient. I also got to use the self-service lockers, different sizes available even big ones to contain my 28 inch luggage. Mind that you need a valid train ticket to access the locker as it is located within the gate.

According to my experience, Amsterdam Centraal Station is one of the best internal railway station station. The Station has a nice architecture and facade. It is integrated with the rest of the transportation system therefore it is the central place if you need to transit to other part of Amsterdam. 

It is very clean and modern. of course, it is a very busy railway station

A very clean and tidy station and plenty of ticket machines meaning little or no wait to get tickets. Clear times of trains arriving/leaving and Euro 5.50 to get to Schiphol Airport. A variety of shops and once out the main entrance you are straight into the hustle and bustle of Amsterdam.

Very reasonable 10 Euro for an audio tour of the palace. I would highly recommend to anyone! There are kids audio options and if you are really interested in something you can get even more information via audio. The staff are SUPER friendly and there is a cloakroom for your bag and coats.

Beautiful palace that just inspires awe at every turn. To be among such great pieces of work and history is truly humbling.

This place is very befitting of the title "Royal" and is a marvel with the intricacies of the paintings, sculptures, and works of art scattered throughout.

The admission is fairly priced and comes with a free audio tour that provides nuggets of information on the various rooms and history associated with them. Additionally, the tour gives you options of learning the extra facts relating to a sculpture and/or painting.

I really feel like you could come here 2 or 3 times and still learn or see something new here. Absolutely beautiful in hundreds of ways, witnessing this building and all its treasures firsthand is something spectacular. Pictures don't do it justice.

Anything to do with Amsterdam is already good enough for me. Add to that a chance to take in the Royal Palace, the cherry has been placed on my tourism cake. 

Taking a walking tour was well worth it. We learned so much from our guide, it truly made the experience memorable.

If you have the time, why not do it? The architecture that surrounds the area alone, is well worth it.

First of all, if you're into interesting buildings, you can never go wrong with palaces. This type of buildings are always the place of many interesting stories. This city hall turned palace during the reign of Napoleon is no different. Large halls full of exquisite art and the most expensive furniture give you a peek at how it is to be a dignitary in the Netherlands. The excellent audio tour (with a special version for kids) in a dozen languages that allows you to wander through the halls in your own tempo makes it a five star to visit. No rush, just interesting history.

It’s amazing that you’re able to walk in and explore the actual Royal Palace! There’s a wide range of different rooms - all with unique snippets of history attached. Joy for the whole family - would definitely recommend visiting it if you’re in Amsterdam.

Unlike many other sightseeing places, this one is very kid- and English-friendly. Kids get their own audio guide and a little necklace to fill out to keep them interested. For adults there are various language available - including English.

An interesting historic site. Pretty and well preserved. Some interesting buildings and historic background.
For most visitors will only amount to a walk through. Probably a half hour or less visit for most people.
Worth a visit if in the area.

This is the perfect place if you need a little break from the Amsterdam city center without actually leaving it. 
A small church in a quiet backyard, only open until 5pm. It has some restricted areas that are reserved for the inhabitants of the buildings, but it's a nice spot for having a snack on a bench in the sun.

A quaint and secret getaway in the heart of the city. On a sunny day, well worth the stroll for some peace. The history itself is pretty interesting and worth visiting for. We couldn’t visit the secret Catholic Church but would have been cool to do so.
A spot of beauty and calm in the otherwise busy and noisy centre of Amsterdam. Also historically relevant. Always worth a visit. Take care, the entrance closes at 17:30.
Beautiful, serene and not as crowded as most other tourist attractions. Plus you learn some history. AND the area has lots of awesome bookstores, shops and cafés

This is a really beautiful old church. It's kind of sad that it isn't used anymore as a church. I found it fascinating that there seems to be burial chambers under the entire floor. And a copy of Rembrandt's and Saskia's marriage record on display.

We weren't allowed in, because there was some exhibition. We wanted to see the church nothing more. The exhibition cost 10 euros, to my mind it doesn't worth this money. We managed to see many pictures of this exhibition and they weren't beautiful at all. I recommend to see it when there is no any exhibition.

You have to give a church 4 stars. The sheer effort of building it deserves that. Even if it is a bit dour.... grim might be a better word. Or perhaps austere... You can decide. Its not unmissable. You'll enjoy the other sights of Amsterdam if you miss this. It won't change your life if you do go. You might feel a bit colder. Or wish you'd been in a cafe.. Or a bar.. I don't know. You do. I went and explored it. I shan't feel the need to do so again.

Amsterdam by night at its finest! There’s something magical about this place - I had to be there during a red moon that made it even more special. But from any angel this place is simply beautiful - do not miss it.

Cool church. Plays a Chime I believe at the top of every hour. Looks awesome over the skyline. All of Amsterdam is beautiful. Next to red light district and next to a lot of bars and food when your ready to do other things
Great museum, I did felt like in Egypt inside, like an archeologist. There were a few people working on some pottery pieces trying to fix them, they talked to us very briefly, that was cool.

This museum has a nice archeological collection, from antiquities, to Egyptian artifacts, to the local stuff. They have a "hotspot" where visitors can try their hand a piecing together ceramics from an excavation, which was awesome. The standard collection was organized by theme, as in war, trade, etc, not chronologically, which made it a little difficult to get an oversight.

The temporary exhibition was awesome, lots of photos from the beginning of the 20th century and from all over the world. I can only assume they'll replace it with something as interesting. All in all, if you like archeology, it's certainly worth a visit.
It looked like a daughter of Leiden archeological museum. Small but a good collection worth visiting! Had Roman, Greek, Egypt and other collections

There's a lot of interesting history here, but it's difficult to find your way around the museum. I'm sure I missed a few things, and I got lost along the way. Definitely bring a map with you throughout the museum.
Great place to see lots of interesting displays of ancient objects. Friendly staff and a great cafe. Visit the Archaeology Hot Spot and help put 17th and 18th century pottery back together

An excellent overview of Jewish culture and the impact the 1930-40s had. The ground floor  explains different items, traditions and rituals with in-depth information. 

The upper floor is dedicated to the impact of the 1930-40s. Please note that this isn't the Holocaust museum, that is only a few minutes walk away and included with the same ticket.

I had lunch here and that was great! Friendly staff and a delicious pear tart (highly recommended!!).

Without a doubt, one of the best museums in Amsterdam, with a large and varied exhibition. Nearby is a part of the museum, made specifically for children. The museum is located in the former historic Jewish part of the city, next to the largest synagogue, which is also part of this museum complex.
Very interesting museum with a wide selection different pieces. It's bigger than you think. I was on my way out and discovered a whole other wing.

Well worth a visit though you will need to spend several hours of reading various exhibits to get the most out of this place.  Reasonably expensive but the tickets dis allow us to see other attractions that we did not have time to visit during our short stay.

Educational and informative.  The staff are very helpful.

The cost of a ticket gives access to four 'attractions' within the city's Jewish quarter, which in itself is very reasonable. This museum was very insightful, provided lots of information, quite interactive and educational for visitors keen to learn about the religion, and the people's history in Amsterdam and the rest of the country. We thoroughly enjoyed it, thank you.

When I Arrived I wasn't very overwhelmed, It was a very basic tour and I was beginning to be thankful that I had a Amsterdam pass and didn't waste any money on this..Until we arrive in the large studio and a Expert was giving a talk on how paints used to be made and demonstrated in front of us how Rembrandt would have had himself or students make the paint. It was like watching alchemy and it was in my opinion it's saving grace. Also a beautiful Selection of art adorning the walls. And grab an Audio tour but if the expert is showing you stuff in the Studio just keep quiet and watch!

Cute little museum, with live demonstrations of a couple aspects of an artists life from back in his time. Nicely decorated and plenty of Rembrandt's work to see, well worth a visit if you're a fan. Quite small but priced accordingly. Don't bother buying tickets online to save time; there's no separate line for entering so you'll have to wait in the ticket line either way.

Well, it's an old house in which someone famous lived. If you're really into him, into art (but studying art, not just admiring art), you're gonna like it. But otherwise go see his masterpieces at other museums. Not my scene. High lights: great staff and structure, very welcoming.

For me this was the educational highlight in Amsterdam. With an established love for details this house shows an authentic approach to the life and work of Rembrandt. The employees were SO nice and we could ask a lot of questions about the artistic techniques and the historic background. Furthermore the demonstrations of etching/printing and the mixing of colors were amazing! Thank you for an amazing visit. And shoutout to the compassionate employees who were so helpful and friendly.

It pays off to visit his house and see how it looked, I am amazed with his personality and lifestyle.
Genius is the right word.
Plan this in your schedule.
This was a very fun experience. It was really big and lots of superstars were there. I would  highly recommend taking a camera with you because you can take beautiful photos. 🤳

Madame Tussauds Amsterdam is the cool place to visit. It's very well organized. They also have captain marvel theme for kids and for the Marvel fans. They have nice art work and statue of lot of famous celebrity from film industry, music industry , sports industry. It was nice visit.
Great place. Worth a visit. Expensive but I guess it is not cheap to make and perhaps even royalties paid for the characters and figures. Children loved it too.

Had a lot of fun in this place. We went in January and it was mostly empty which was nice. Lots of interactive displays and cool things to look at. It was better than I expected. Go during off hours; I could see this place not being nearly as good if it were crowded.

Fun! Most of the wax figures look quite young so might need to be updated at some point. First Madame Tussauds I've been to. Sent a photo of me with Ryan Gosling to a friend and found out by chance she was in Amsterdam too so that was a wonderful surprise 😂
This was a very fun experience. It was really big and lots of superstars were there. I would  highly recommend taking a camera with you because you can take beautiful photos. 🤳

Madame Tussauds Amsterdam is the cool place to visit. It's very well organized. They also have captain marvel theme for kids and for the Marvel fans. They have nice art work and statue of lot of famous celebrity from film industry, music industry , sports industry. It was nice visit.
Great place. Worth a visit. Expensive but I guess it is not cheap to make and perhaps even royalties paid for the characters and figures. Children loved it too.

Had a lot of fun in this place. We went in January and it was mostly empty which was nice. Lots of interactive displays and cool things to look at. It was better than I expected. Go during off hours; I could see this place not being nearly as good if it were crowded.

Fun! Most of the wax figures look quite young so might need to be updated at some point. First Madame Tussauds I've been to. Sent a photo of me with Ryan Gosling to a friend and found out by chance she was in Amsterdam too so that was a wonderful surprise 😂

Not a typical ice cream that you can get anywhere. It is softer and tastes a bit like whipped cream, and you can get only one flavour. 
One of the best desserts ever, I come here every time when I am in Amsterdam! Can't wait to be back! 😍
Excellent super-creamy ice creams, great value by Amsterdam standards, and judging by the queues of Dutch people out of the door, something of a local institution!
It's not ice cold like a regular ice cream, more like the texture of whipping cream, but super delicious!!!
ice cream is great of course but they only accept cash 😒

Great vanilla ice-cream based on an apparently secret family recipe. Definetly worth a try, especially considering the reasonable price.
The shop area is really small specifically Ice-cream zone. I think it is worth a try if you are an ice-cream lover.
Great Chinese restaurant.  Really fast service and food was superb.  Would recommend the chicken and cashew nut that i had on visiting as it was very very moreish
Tasty Surinamese-Chinese fusion. Reasonable prices for the area. Nice and good English speaking service.

Lovely Chinese restaurant. The service was very fast. We ordered and had our drinks and meals within 5mins. Food was good as was the staff. Place was bust with people coming and going all the time. Lots of locals use this restaurant which was a positive for us.
As cheap as it gets, and the food is really great. Get the super spicy sauces to add! I go there very often, for lunch or dinner. Hartily recommended!
Peking duck wasn't crispy and the small bones were only partially removed, creating an illusion of safety. In general rather low quality food. Attracts loud clients: singing party goers and the like.

It is really a cozy and small restaurant. The staff is very friendly and food in general is amazing. I really love this place and I would say this Thai restaurant is one of the best Thai restaurants in Amsterdam. Noted: they only accept cash so better bring enough cash before you come.

Wonderfully inexpensive, fresh and tasty. It's a small cozy spot with attentive ladies checking regularly on you. Very cute. They have a nice rapport with the customers. I had Tom yum Pak - vegetarian (tofu) hot sour soup. And a green curry. Yum

Hole in the wall much? Literally. Settled in a little store front with doors that look like they’re made for hobbits. The mini sliding doors slide open and you’re in a little ten to fifteen seater with a kitchen smelling of basil fish sauce and other beautiful aromas I can’t pin point exactly. 

We ask for a menu and the nice lady greets us and asks us to sit even though we’re going for take out. It was late, they’re closing soon and were not tryna be those people. We order the pad Thai , red beef curry with bamboo shoots. Both items were exceptional. The service was fast and again the food was the best we’ve had in a while as far as Thai goes. Real lime leaves and whole stocks of basil are used generously to boast flavor in their dishes. Curries are beautifully balanced with sweetness from coconut and hints of sour to spicy hit your palate. This is some real good food no matter where you are coming from in the world. Even Thailand I put my word on it.
Great food, great service, great price.

This restaurant is a short walk from Nieuwmarkt metro station or a couple of canal bridges away from Red Light District. It is not easy to spot from distance and is kinda lost in narrow streets of the area. Food here is as authentic as it can get and that too for a reasonable price. Highly recommended if you fancy Thai food during your stay. Don't forget to bring some cash with you, this is a cash only place.

Our hotel recommended Greetje for dinner and boy did it not disappoint. Their service, attention to detail and overall demeanor was top notch, not to mention the food. Doing the tasting menu of all the appetizers, selecting your own main followed by a sampling of 6 desserts was seriously next level. Every bite was incredible. Would definitely recommend for a nice evening out.

Finger liking good dutch cuisine!
For real, surprisingly good! The food is delicious and rooted in the tradition of dutch cuisine. One of the best restaurants I've found in my (unluckily too short) visit to Amsterdam. The table service is extremely professional, but warm and fun at the same time thanks to the nice and gentle staff. Pretty expensive (a bit too much probably), but still 100% worth it!

Excellent meal, great service and a friendly attentive staff. It is a little pricey, but well worth it to have a delicious taste of Dutch quisine.
I had the rabbit and my wife had the veal. Both were great. Don't leave without a cappuccino and some mulled wine for the road.

Lovely restaurant friendly staff. Food was wonderfully presented tasted great but was very rich. Home cooked bread was great with the different butters. Picture taken was the duck breast dish.  An amuse bouche was served to which was a lovely surprise from the chef. Would definitely recommend for authentic local dishes. However if you are thinking of taking an elderly person (or unsteady on feet) there are steep stairs to the seating area and more when you go to the toilet.

Really a nice Dutch food experience here
Very detail explanation of food which was very tasty as well
Love it! Five stars! :)

(Unfortunately, the light there was too dim, can’t take good pictures)
A cozy place for drinks since it was near our home. Like this place is near to the gym I went to as well. Overall a pleasant place to relax.
Stumbled across this restaurant and glad we did. Excellent Dutch food with great staff and a busy lively atmosphere to match. Will be back.
Needed soup to go. Had to get my own container but they humored me! Great food and service. I'm not a fan of the old fashioned Dutch rye bread, but that isn't their fault!
Ribs were as good as 10yeas ago. Good menu for small or greater appetite.
Great food and friendly staff well worth a visit

Frankly speaking, the staff are not well trained, they are not familiar with the products. Slow in response, the level of service hooks with the amount of budget. The bigger budget, more choices and better services. If u are spending small money then they will just show you 3-5 choices. They are so hurry to make the deal so to move on to next customers/ visitor groups. The diamond price there is not carrying out the same level of services. If u want a 201 facets, go n visit them. If u want a normal 57 facets I will suggest to give a pass and take a look at the stores in Antwerpen.
Best place in Europe for fair prices and excellent consultation!!! Thanks to Danielle for her outstanding support... always a good memory in mind.
Very fine place. It's like a museum where's everything is on sale.

Really memorable trip with family. Was planning on surprising my wife with a gift and was in talks with a senior staff months before my trip. She recognized me and got the shortlisted list.
They gave a gift for my daughter as well.
Loved the experience! Thank you!

Me and my girlfriend took the tour in italian with Simone Pilla: this turned out to be the highlight of our stay in Amsterdam! First we had an interesting tour of the shop , where he explained us the four C's of diamonds evaluation and showed us the cut and polishment procedure. Afterwards he showed us a lot of diamonds exhibiting the very different characteristics which he first theoretically described. I highly recommend the tour to both people who are willing to shop and to people who just want to learn something new!

Heineken Experience is a must see for beer lovers, even if you particularly do not like Heineken itself. The tour is full of awesome artifacts from the original brewery and is full of informational portions as well.

The flow of the tour is great and there is lots of space between the various groups save for a few parts. The room where you 'become a Heineken' was really awesome and the beer they give you after really hits the spot. Something about walking all day and a cold refreshing beer just can't be beat.

Lastly, the ending part where you redeem your 2 beers is pretty cool. Typical bar type area with quick service (they only serve Heineken of course). Cool music and vibes really make this pop off. 

Also, there is an area before the end where you can create a custom Heineken label and have it put on a bottle for a souvenir. We ended up going with the 2 for 10 Euros, which wasn't too bad in my opinion. Definitely pleased!

This tour is a must see even if you vaguely have any interest in beer. This your will deepen your appreciation for the process of beer making. When you are done with the tour the tour top bar has some delicious food for sale & love entertainment. We actually did not want to leave.

Amazing feeling to visit the Heineken Experience where it all started and revisit the legacy of such big brand. A must go place if you are visiting Amsterdam.
I've visited the Heineken Experience as the first brewery in Europe. At the time of our visit (end of December) it was not crowded but don't be bothered by the long queue at the main entrance. Guess the experience comes as part if the Amsterdam plan. The tour staff were well aware and talked with the visitors about the details. While We were all ears about the brand's history, logo and the beer making process. They prepare an amazing tour with attractive plans for their visitors. The real highlights of the experience were the path that took the visitors up and down to the tasting hall. At the end part you can try 2 glass of beer. The beer tasting experience was wonderful and attractive. the beer was really fresh. Highly recommended to visit!!!

Great experience. Having gone to the Guinness Factory i had high expectations and the Heineken Experience while fun wasn’t the same. That being said it has its own special history and I enjoyed myself. 

The first couple rooms were crowded, it was tough to see all the information. After, once the crowd was spread out the rest of the tour was awesome. The beer experience ride was exciting and felt like a mini roller coaster.

The gift shop at the end was also great with tons of cool stuff.

Anyone in Amsterdam should definitely check it out!

We visited on a Saturday afternoon in April.  It cost 21 Euros and was a nice way to spend a leisurely afternoon.  The tour is informative and the docents are very nice.  The bottling experience is a nice touch.  But the beer tasting and the two glasses at the end were a nice close to the tour.  The attached picture show two things to be cautious of in the area: bicyclists and motorcyclists....they are everywhere and pop out unexpectedly.

This museum has been a wonderful surprise! 
We were not expecting to see so many interesting and beautiful pieces of art. The museum is really big and it’s hosting a lot of modern artists. Also the building itself is really cool. It worth a visit, and it takes more time than we expected to see it.
As modern art museums go - one of the best. We had a ... local brownie ... beforehand and took in all the amazing stuff. Highly recommend!

One of the best museum's in Europe. A pleasant surprise of modern pieces which have been creatively placed throughout the expansive space. The exterior design has a unique and expansive swooping roof which adds to the visual appeal of this modern museum.
You could spend a weekend here...there is art for every taste. Really a must for modern art lovers when in Amsterdam. Can't wait to revisit!

The building has very nice architecture. If you like going to lots of museums in the Netherlands and you live here I highly advise you get a Museumkaart. I've been here multiple times and the exhibitions are always great.
Beautiful park, very large! Seems like all of Amsterdam is chilling here when its hot.
Love it! I go there almost every day and it's huge and great! There lots of cafe's, playgrounds and the lakes are beautiful! It's great!
It's the heaven itself for those who love chill, nature or sports. Being there was the best moment of my trip so far.
Love this park as it is an amazing place & whenever it's sunny I feel like going to this place. Also there are few places around the park where you can just relax & chill .
Nice place for a walk in the centre of the city. The lakes not very clean from garbage. You can find some shops to drink or eat something.

This a beautiful spot right by the Amstel river. 
It is a pleasent walk from the Amsterdam RAI metro stop. The walk goes through Amstel park then along the the river.
Nice wind mill by the side of the park and amstel river

Beautiful classic Dutch windmill - looks great too in silhouette from the other side of the river.
The parked car of the inhabitants is somewhat of a disfigurement though.
At the southern end of Amstelpark. There are 8 windmills in Amsterdam and this one is one of the ones in a quieter parts and you can walk right up to it.
Good-looking building, although it cannot be visited inside (it looks like someone lives there).
Great place. Super low key and family style. Meals are great and always super fast. Just a huge menu and sometimes it’s hard to choose
Amazing place! Lots of good food for a small price! Loved it!
Very simple, superlocal place. The food is Surinamese Chinese, which may surprise the tourist. The staff is very friendly. Try the 'pom'.
First time back since my student days (way way back). Brilliant price/quality, very friendly staff. Will be back!
Very delicious and cheap food! Portions are huge - remember it! Service is very friendly!

Street food in India is far better than this place.. the roti was like floor mat... The dishes did not have any taste in them.. please don't bring India's name down with such a low class food and service in a tourist place. Please work on the food quality, taste and service. Otherwise better close this place down and avoid embarrassment.

Nice people, great service. As far as somebody told me, they serve comfy food from the south of India. The food came very fast and it was very interesting because you can sense all unique flavors. A little greasy but it didn't stop me from eating too much!

They make delivery riders wait for an hour and aren’t considerate of the time of customers who order online. Customers who order online pay the same amount of money as those who eat at the restaurant. You should provide good service to all your customers!

This place makes like you're sitting in India - excellent authentic food in a lunchroom setting, all for a very friendly price. It tastes that great you forget that it's vegetarian altogether! Not a romantic date spot but perfect for groups, or your best mates.

One can never describe how a south Indian feels after indulging in yummy, authentic south Indian dishes in a land far away from home. It's simply elevating! I was on a trip to Amsterdam from France, and how could i not pop in for a meal? The food was great, the service was friendly and the place totally filled with our homies 😂. Looked as though I'd been teleported back to India. Will definitely come again.

Absolutely amazing experience! Dinner was delicious, I had fish as my main delicious, the service was excellent. We go thru life not truly appreciating the gifts we are given as individuals.  Experiencing a meal complete darkness forces the other senses to come alive. Thank you! I would recommend this to everyone to try, you will definitely be pleased.
Amazing experience!  It's hard to describe in words.  The staff was amazing.  The food was so good.  Be ready for something you have never experienced before.  No words to describe it.
What a great experience! The food was delicious and the staff very friendly and helpful. If you haven't been here, you have to try this!!!

I was treated to a weekend in Amsterdam by my wife. She booked us a table for my birthday meal. Out of all the trips and activities she arranged, this is the one I was looking forward to the most. And we weren't let down. We found the staff polite and welcoming as soon as we arrived. Our waiter on the night was Luke and he was brilliant. He guided us to our table and explained what we were to expect. We accepted his challenge to find and pour a glass of water haha.
The food was really nice and we found that it's true about loosing one sense and others heightening. 
Reading previous comments, I have to slightly agree about the costs of drinks being high (we had 2 glasses of wine each and a bottle of water for €34.50) but it didn't negatively affect our evening.
Would we go again? Definitely.
Would we recommend to others? 100% yes!
Thank you for making my birthday a special day.
Phil & Natalie 
English fans

Great experience! We got the premium dinner. The menu is a surprise and you only know what you've had at the end, and I liked the extra challenge of trying to pour glasses of water in the dark. Friendly staff and they paid special care to your dietary requirements . The food was quite good - but you're really there for the experience.
